{
    "topic": "Launch Scripts",
    "pageNumber": "1",
    "type": "Launch Scripts",
    "definition": {
        "text": "There are a number of scripts to help make lauching Superalgos easier and feel more native. The eventual goal is to make Superalgos feel like any other program installed on an operating system.",
        "updated": 1620052836275
    },
    "paragraphs": [
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "The current solution is to use two sets of scripts:",
            "updated": 1620051940824
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "One set to execute node run and actually start Superalgos.",
            "updated": 1620051973593
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "The second to create and place shortcuts to these launch scripts for convenient use.",
            "updated": 1620052849823
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "Due to the nature of scripts, there are different scripts for each type of operating system. The following page includes a description of each script and what it accomplishes.",
            "updated": 1620052862888
        },
        {
            "style": "Note",
            "text": "All launch related scripts are held in the Lauch-Scripts folder in the main Superalgos directory.",
            "updated": 1620504577923
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": ""
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Basic Launch Scripts"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "These scripts execute the node run command to start Superalgos. They can be run from command line calls or a file browser.",
            "updated": 1620052707525
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Windows "
        },
        {
            "style": "Json",
            "text": "launch-windows.bat"
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Linux"
        },
        {
            "style": "Json",
            "text": "launch-linux.sh"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "This script uses the x-terminal-emulator command for maximum compatiblity across linux flavors."
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Mac"
        },
        {
            "style": "Important",
            "text": "Collaborator needed.",
            "updated": 1620052924921
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": ""
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Desktop/Launcher Shortcut Scripts",
            "updated": 1620052680945
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "These scripts automatically create and place shortcuts to the launch scripts. They can be run from the command line or file browser.",
            "updated": 1620504518909
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Windows"
        },
        {
            "style": "Json",
            "text": "create-shortcut-windows.bat",
            "updated": 1620053219653
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "Currently this script only places a shortcut on the user's desktop. Revision in progress to also place shortcut in the start menu.",
            "updated": 1620053366379
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Ubuntu",
            "updated": 1620053330166
        },
        {
            "style": "Json",
            "text": "create-shortcut-ubuntu.sh",
            "updated": 1620504490683
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "This script places shortcuts within the user's launcher and desktop. Shortcuts are placed in the following locations:",
            "updated": 1620504828523
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "~/Desktop/Superalgos.desktop"
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "~/.local/share/applications/Superalgos.desktop"
        },
        {
            "style": "Note",
            "text": "After running create-shortcut-ubuntu.sh the launcher shortcut will work out of the box. There are a few additional steps to set up the desktop shortcut. The following section will walk you through these steps.",
            "updated": 1620505700097
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "First, desktop icons need to be enabled within the Tweaks app.",
            "updated": 1620505123531
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "Check if Tweaks is installed.",
            "updated": 1620505145330
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "If not go to Ubuntu Software.",
            "updated": 1620505149642
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "Install Tweaks.",
            "updated": 1620505153965
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "Open Tweaks.",
            "updated": 1620505158082
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "Under extensions turn on Desktop Icons"
        },
        {
            "style": "Gif",
            "text": " GIFs/Superalgos/Docs/launch-scripts/enable-ubuntu-shortcut.gif"
        },
        {
            "style": "Success",
            "text": "If you do not see the desktop shortcut appear right away you may need to restart your computer.",
            "updated": 1620505754854
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "Finally, you will need to enable the desktop shortcut.",
            "updated": 1620505790748
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "Right click Superalgos.desktop and select Allow Launching.",
            "updated": 1620505813768
        },
        {
            "style": "Gif",
            "text": "GIFs/Superalgos/Docs/launch-scripts/allow-launching.gif",
            "updated": 1620505894840
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Mac"
        },
        {
            "style": "Important",
            "text": "Collaborator needed."
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Uninstall Shortcut Scripts",
            "updated": 1620053489270
        },
        {
            "style": "Important",
            "text": "No scripts started yet. Manual deletion required.",
            "updated": 1620053525531
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Manually Unistall Shortcuts",
            "updated": 1620506058024
        },
        {
            "style": "Subtitle",
            "text": "Ubuntu"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "Open a terminal and run the following command:"
        },
        {
            "style": "Javascript",
            "text": "rm ~/Desktop/Superalgos.desktop && rm ~/.local/share/applications/Superalgos.desktop"
        }
    ]
}